titleStmt.title: Exceding ioyfull newes from the Earle of Warwicke wherein is declared his resolution, concerning the Kings Majesties desires, to have the Navy resigned to him, likewise the Parliaments determination, concerning the same. Also, a true relation of proceedings from Yorke and Beverly- shewing, the great power and strength there raysed, against the Parliament and Hul, under the command of the Lord Carnarvon, Lord Rich, Captaine Butler, Colonell Fielding, Colonell Lunsford, likewise, the bounty of the clergy, and of the gentry in Yorksheire, tending to the encreasing and managing of, these unhappy proceedings Iohn, Brow. Cler. Parl.
